                            <comment id="14978472" author="beobal" created="Wed, 28 Oct 2015 14:10:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I agree with your diagnosis. I&apos;ve updated &lt;tt&gt;SIM::reloadIndex&lt;/tt&gt; to request a reload task from every index, and to execute all non-null tasks. This is inline with previous (i.e. pre 3.0) behaviour, but it did require removing the call to &lt;tt&gt;setMetadata&lt;/tt&gt; from &lt;tt&gt;CassandraIndex::getMetadataReloadTask&lt;/tt&gt; or else it would attempt to re-create the index cfs. I actually think this is the right thing to do anyway as indexes are never modified, only dropped and recreated, so setting up the index cfs should definitely only happen once.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;While I was there, I&apos;ve added some clarification to the javadocs for &lt;tt&gt;Index.Indexer&lt;/tt&gt; in a separate commit.&lt;/p&gt;

